<item>
            <title>[SPARK-14322] Use treeAggregate instead of reduce in OnlineLDAOptimizer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-14322</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;OnlineLDAOptimizer uses &lt;tt&gt;RDD.reduce&lt;/tt&gt; in two places where it could use treeAggregate.  This can cause scalability issues.  This should be an easy fix.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is also a bug since it modifies the first argument to reduce, so we should use aggregate or treeAggregate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See this line: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/f12f11e578169b47e3f8b18b299948c0670ba585/mllib/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/mllib/clustering/LDAOptimizer.scala#L452&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/f12f11e578169b47e3f8b18b299948c0670ba585/mllib/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/mllib/clustering/LDAOptimizer.scala#L452&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
and a few lines below it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
